Susan A wrote a review Nov 2018
Langley, Canada7 contributions5 helpful votes
Best on the Beach
This is a top notch hotel that excels in service. We enjoyed our 5 night stay here thoroughly. It is so close to the beach which is extremely clean. There are a lot of seafood restaurants nearby but not much else. The hotel offers a delightful buffet breakfast and there are restaurants on site. The rooftop bar and restaurant are worth a visit. The view is amazing. It is an easy half hour taxi to HoiAn. I would recommend staying in danang for its beaches, quietness and cleanliness.
Xin chào smanders2018, Thank you very much for taking the time to leave such a lovely review of your stay with us at A La Carte Da Nang Beach hotel. I was delighted to read that you enjoyed your stay. I hope that we will have the chance to welcome you back to À La Carte again soon. Sincerely, The A La Carte management team.
MeoMap wrote a review Nov 2018
Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam22 contributions6 helpful votes
Price was right but overall, this is mediocre and only going to go down
Arrived at the normal check-in time....the lobby is FILLED with people ready to check in. The staff - overwhelmed. Too many people wanting rooms, too few staff to check in...and a lot of mostly Chinese nationals who were very very rude (pushing, shoving, shouting). Finally, we get a room - smelly! We told the check in staff that the room was very smelly, they said nothing they could do. We asked for another room, again, spoke with the hotel manager who said: yes, but we have to wait an hour. Okay, so we get the room - NOISY (the beach side, which we paid extra to have, is quiet...the other sides: construction all around). We take it...noisy we can tolerate, smell, you cannot, not with 2 young children. Meals: a huge buffet area...the same pushy Chinese were there…
Date of stay: July 2018
1 Helpful vote
Xin chao MeoMap, Thank you for taking the time to advice us of your stay at A La Carte Da Nang Beach hotel. I would like to express my most sincere apologies for your unpleasant experience. We strive to provide service excellence but regrettably, we seem to have fallen short of our usual high standards on this occasion. We have assured that the matter has been discussed with relative department to ensure that we provide you with a better level of service next time you visit us. Thank you once again for your valuable feedback, and we hope to have the opportunity to welcome you again in the future. Sincerely, The A La Carte management team.
